gomodel:SYNGO_2546  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"GR and MR labeling at asymmetrical synapses\"\n- \"MR-ir and GR-ir was expressed in pre- and postsynaptic sites. Qualitative examination of asymmetrical synapses revealed both GR-ir and MR-ir (MA1-620 and rMR1-18 1D5) at the PSD (Fig. 6B-D) and MR-ir at the presynaptic terminal (Fig. 6D), compared to the primary antibody omitted PSD (Fig. 6A).\"\n\nFig.7: \"Quantitative analysis of labeling at postsynaptic density of asymmetrical synapses\"\n- \"Planned contrasts between the groups revealed a significant difference between the primary antibody omitted control and both MRs and GR (t=10.496; p<.001).\". Experimental description: \"20 male Sprague-Dawley rats with intact adrenal glands were used in this study\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2546" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

